  "text": "Although the overall satisfaction level was quite high (95%) for implant-retained mandibular overdenture compared to conventional complete dentures in accordance with Boerrigter (1998). [CITATION_1] No demographic variables were related to the overall satisfaction at a statistically significant level. These results are in agreement with those of Maria E Geertman, Marinus AJ van Waas (1996). [CITATION_2] The present study reported that 89% of the patients were satisfied with the appearance of implant-retained overdenture which was in accordance with Chang et al (1994).",
